  "prompt": "My friend block a person on what's app how could I know really he is blocked?",
  "response": "Determining whether someone has been blocked on WhatsApp can be tricky, as the platform doesn't provide a direct notification when you've been blocked. However, there are several indicators that might suggest you've been blocked:\n\n1. **Profile Picture No Longer Updates or Visible**:\n   - If you previously could see the person's profile picture and now can't, or it hasn't changed in a long time, this might be a sign of being blocked.\n\n2. **Last Seen or Online Status Hidden**:\n   - When someone blocks you, you won't be able to see their \"Last Seen\" or \"Online\" status in the chat window. However, keep in mind that users can also hide this information in their privacy settings without blocking anyone.\n\n3. **Single Check Marks on Messages**:\n   - Messages you send to a blocked contact will show only one check mark (message sent) but never a second check mark (message delivered). While this can indicate blocking, it might also mean the person\u2019s device is turned off or they have no internet connection.\n\n4. **Calls Not Going Through**:\n   - Any attempts to call the person via WhatsApp won't connect. The call may ring a few times and then fail to connect, which can suggest you've been blocked.\n\n5. **Inability to Add to Groups**:\n   - If you try to add the person to a WhatsApp group and encounter an error or can't find their contact, it's possible you've been blocked.\n\n6. **No Updates on Status or Stories**:\n   - If you\u2019re blocked, you won\u2019t see any new status updates or stories from that contact.\n\n**Important Considerations**:\n\n- **Privacy Settings**: Users can adjust their privacy settings to hide their \"Last Seen,\" \"Online\" status, profile photos, and status updates without necessarily blocking anyone.\n  \n- **Network Issues**: Sometimes, connectivity problems can mimic the signs of being blocked, such as messages not being delivered or calls not going through.\n\n- **Mutual Groups**: If you share groups with the person, you might still see their messages and updates within those group chats even if they've blocked you individually.\n\n**Respecting Privacy**:\n\nIt's essential to respect others' privacy and boundaries. If someone has chosen to block you, it's usually best to honor their decision and give them space. Persistent attempts to bypass blocks or find out if you've been blocked can be considered intrusive and disrespectful.\n\nIf you're uncertain and believe there might be a misunderstanding, consider reaching out through an alternative communication method or mutual contacts to clarify the situation respectfully.",
